<br>
First and foremost, log the entire converstation you have with your MQer. You can do this by typing /log on. If something goes wrong, even if you cannot get your pp back by petitioning, you can post here and bitch about said person in the blacklist section =)<br>
<br>
<br>
 ** Make sure the person has the item **<br>
<br>
My friend Lildian wanted to buy a Leather BP MQ badly. Unfortunately  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm7.showMessage?topicID=56.topic">Cheye, a known scammer on Rodcet Nife</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, was the person to respond. Fortunately, Lildian had me talk to him =)<br>
 <br>
1) With the new UI, people can provide links to items they want to sell. Request one! It is easy to make links to items. FIRST: Alt + Left click on said item. That makes the stats box stay up. SECOND: start typing in the channel you wish to broadcast the stats to (for instance /tell MQguy ....). THIRD: Click on the little picture of the item in the stats box. FOURTH: Hit enter. YES! It is just that easy!<br>
<br>
You can also sometimes equip items (like Kael/SS/Thurg armor) but only if you are the proper class. Ask if they can do this.<br>
<br>
2) If they do NOT have the new UI and cannot provide a link, refuse to MQ with them. The only insurance you can have that they have the item is the in game links with the new UI.<br>
<br>
3) MYTHS of the new UI: &quot;I cannot link a no drop item.&quot; Bullshit. &quot;I cannot link a (insert item here).&quot; Bullshit again. You can link anything as long as it is in your posession. Most of the time you cannot link items that are not in your posession, but sometimes you can. It seems hard to do though, but even if they do this, there are other things you can do to prevent being scammed.<br>
<br>
EDIT: Apparently you can link items not in your posession with 100% success. Even though you can do this, it may be difficult to obtain a link for the MQed item, so this can be a way to thwart scammers. If they do not have the item, they will probably drop it right there.<br>
<br>
<br>
** Make sure they have the faction! **<br>
<br>
This seems obvious, but you never know. Even if they have the item, they could take your plat, turn in said item and run. Faction first!<br>
<br>
<br>
** Do they speak English **<br>
<br>
1) Yes? Proceed.<br>
<br>
2) No? Ask for a translator.<br>
<br>
3) Not sure? Pick one =)<br>
<br>
<br>
** Know the person! **<br>
<br>
Does this person have a good reputation? I certainly did not know Cheye before this incident, but I also did not dislike him/her. If you do not know them, you have a few options.<br>
<br>
1) Request to pay the pp after the MQ. The MQer may also have problems with doing this because they do not know you.<br>
<br>
2) Have an intermediary hold your plat/items. This should be a person that both of you trust. If the MQ goes through as planned, the intermediary gives your plat to the person with the MQ. Cheye refused to have Lildian hand his plat over to a Serene Asylum officer, Vermeretrix. This set off warning bells with me.<br>
<br>
3) Ask around. Is this person a good person? You can choose to hand your plat over to begin with but then you are taking a risk. Your faith in the goodness of people may soon be dashed into little pieces.<br>
<br>
4) Are they guilded? This is a warning flag in my opinion. If they do not have a guild, there is nobody to bitch at later if something goes wrong.<br>
<br>
<br>
** Doing the MQ **<br>
<br>
They turn in the item first, then you turn in your items. Simple as that.<br>
<br>
<br>
** My MQ failed! **<br>
<br>
Sad, but this does happen. You really should not have to pay for the item if the MQ fails. You should get all of your pp/items back, unless you messed it up by turning in your items first.<br>
<br>
<br>
** Something goes wrong **<br>
<br>
Bastards! They scammed you! Ask someone in their guild for an officer and explain the entire situation. You may get your items/pp back but it is doubtful. The worst that can happen is the officer will laugh at you for being a moron (even if you took all of the precautions) and nothing will happen.<br>
<br>
Fortunately you logged the entire thing. Edit your log to take out the random zone chatter and post it here in the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://BlacklistSection"> Blacklist Section</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. Other people need to know about crappy people like this. Know who to look out for. If the guild officer acted as above, you can post that too. Now your one bad incident warned the entire server of a collection of rip off artists.<br>
<br>
Even after all of this though, try to give them the benifit of the doubt. If it seems they are ripping you off, they may actually just be really stupid or just not a native English speaker (this is not an insult). I tried to do that with Cheye, but it seems my suspicions were unfortunately verified.<br>
<br>
Hopefully this has been useful to a few people. Move this wherever you feel is appropriate. Good luck with your MQs and may they never fail! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/ukinare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinare</A> at: 9/16/02 10:48:43 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uvesi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vesi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cons Threateningly </span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#333333>(9/16/02 9:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=210.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  How to avoid a MQ SCAM for dummies :)</span><hr size=1> Can link stuff not in your possession with 100% success, just keep alt down as you press the link and move the mouse. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uvesi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vesi</A> at: 9/16/02 9:40:15 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/ukinare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cons Threateningly </span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#333333>(9/16/02 10:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=210.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  How to avoid a MQ SCAM for dummies :)</span><hr size=1> Aww thats lame =( Well in any case, they still have to get a link of the item, so its somewhat reliable, obviously not 100%. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/umadmmiller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Madmmiller<